                        <h3 class="card-title py-2" id="card-title">Why are generic drugs cheaper even with the same components?</h3><hr>
                        <p class="card-text">Although generic drug active ingredients are chemically identical to their branded counterparts, they are typically sold at a cheaper price than the brand name drug.</p><br>
                        <br> 
                        <p class="card-text">Generics are less expensive because the drug manufacturer does not have to duplicate the original clinical trials for effectiveness and safety, which lowers the cost to bring the drug to market. </p>
