                        <p class="card-text">In the United States, trademark laws do not allow generic drugs to look exactly like the brand name drug. However, the generic drug must have the same active ingredients.</p>
                        <br>
                        <p class="card-text">Colors, flavors, and certain other inactive ingredients of generic drugs may be different from brand name drugs but the effectiveness of the drug remains the same.</p>
                        
